[2] Colorado
------------
Date: Wed 24 Apr 2013
Source: Pueblo Chieftain [edited]
http://www.chieftain.com/news/local/salmonella-cases-reported-locally/article_90ffb6ea-ac92-11e2-8c50-0019bb2963f4.html

9 children younger than 12 have been infected with salmonella since Easter [31 Mar 2013], the Pueblo City-County Health Department reported Tuesday [23 Apr 2013].

The 1st case was documented during the 1st week of April and the last one this week, according to department spokeswoman Sarah Joseph.

The outbreak is believed to be related to contact with live poultry and baby chicks, according to a news release.

Health department Director Dr. Christine Nevin-Woods said anyone who handles poultry or farm animals should wash their hands afterward, and children should be discouraged from cuddling or kissing chicks or ducklings.

By Loretta Sword <lorettas@chieftain.com>

