[3] Nebraska
------------
Dte:
Source: Lincoln Journal Star [edited]
http://journalstar.com/news/state-and-regional/nebraska/nebraska-kids-had-salmonellosis/article_c977f432-0bd4-556b-8d68-e18b57e3df77.html


Nebraska has had 6 confirmed cases of salmonellosis among children ages 1 to 6 recently, but Nebraska Health and Human Services officials have been unable to confirm a common source of salmonella infection.

This time of year, it could be exposure to live Easter gifts, like baby chicks or ducklings. In fact, 5 of the 6 sick kids had exposure to chicks or ducklings, HHS spokeswoman Leah Bucco-White said in an email. "But we haven't been able to confirm that baby poultry was the source of infection," she wrote.

The cases of 5 girls and one boy are all in eastern and south-central Nebraska. One was hospitalized, later recovered and was released.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Especially in the spring, outbreaks of salmonellosis are reported from exposure to chicks and/or ducklings. ProMED-mail awaits information from CDC regarding the scope of this year's outbreak. - Mod.LL]

[Salmonella carried in the intestines of chicks and ducklings contaminates their environment and the entire surface of the animal. Children can be exposed to the bacteria by simply holding, cuddling, or kissing the birds. Salmonella can cause diarrhea, vomiting, and fever. Some people are more susceptible to infection and will have more severe disease. These people include young children, pregnant women, the elderly, people on chemotherapy, diabetics, and others with weakened immune systems. Approximately 20 percent of cases reported to MDH are hospitalized.

What a shame! Surely the whole point of getting a nice fluffy yellow chick or duck for Easter is to cuddle and kiss it? But parents beware: a toy fluffy chick or rubber duck is safer.

A map showing the states of the USA is at:
http://www.freeworldmaps.net/northamerica/united-states/political.html
For those who don't know their USA geography, Minnesota, Nebraska & Colorado, in that order, are the 2 yellow and one brown states running down diagonally left from the westernmost Great Lake (Lake Superior, so named for being bigger than all others on the continent). - Mod.JW]
